The paper deals with privacy-preserving machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on training neural networks over encrypted data, which is a sub-topic of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed framework also involves the use of functional encryption, which is a cryptographic technique (cs.CY). The paper also involves performance evaluation and security analysis, which are topics related to data science (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE), respectively.
